"title": "8456: obedience, to human authorities",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8456",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture teaches that all people, Christians included, should submit not only to God himself but also to divinely instituted secular authorities.</p>\n<h2>Obedience is owed to rulers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:1–13:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:3\">1TI 2:1–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">TIT 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ expounds this principle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:17\">MRK 12:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:21\">MAT 22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:25\">LUK 20:25</a></p>\n<h2>Obedience is owed to church leaders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Obedience is owed within the household</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:1–6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:5\">PRO 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ sets the example</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:51\">LUK 2:51</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Obedience to secular authority is limited by obedience to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:29\">ACT 5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:19\">ACT 4:19</a></p>",
